attle of Cravant, France":"Cravant, Loiret, Centre-Val de Loire, France","Scotland":"Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Turnbull","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Durham and Northumberland) and Scottish: occupational name for one who herds bulls, from Middle English <i>turne-bole</i>, a compound of Middle English <i>t(o)urnen</i> ‘turn, direct, steer’ + <i>bul(l)e</i> ‘bull’. Compare   Bulman   and <i>Bullard</i>.","Scottish (Roxburghshire): in the Scottish borderlands the name was either confused with or derived from   Trumble  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Bulman","meanings":["English (northern): occupational name for a keeper of a bull or bulls, from Middle English <i>bule</i> ‘bull’ + <i>man</i> ‘man’. In Ireland, this has been a common name in Cork since the 17th century.","In some cases possibly also an Americanized form of German <b>Bullmann</b> (see   Bullman  )."]},{"name":"Trumble","meanings":["English (Lancashire and Yorkshire): from a Middle English personal name <i>T(h)rumbald</i> (Old English <i>Trumbeald</i>, from <i>trum</i> ‘strong’ + <i>beald</i> ‘brave’).","Scottish (of Norman origin): habitational name from Le Tremblay (Eure).","Scottish: variant of   Turnbull  ."]}]},{"name":"Walter","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French personal name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i>, <i>hari</i> ‘army’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England, superseding the native Old English form, <i>Wealdhere</i>. It was a very popular name in medieval England, normally pronounced ‘Water’."],"variants":[{"name":"Walther","meanings":["from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i> ‘army’; name of the famous medieval minnesinger  Walther von der Vogelweide  (  <i>c.</i>1170– <i>c.</i>1230 )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Baron Walter Turnbull - of Minto, Knight was born in 1382, in Minto, Roxburghshire, Scotland, his father, Baron John Turnbull of Minto, was 38 and his mother, Diana Stewart Erskine, was 21. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Lorna Rutherford. He died in 1440, in Scotland, at the age of 58."},"et":{"1382–1440":"1382–1440","1380–Female":"1380–Surnud","1400–Female":"1400–Surnud","1410–1454":"1410–1454","1345–1423":"1345–1423","1361–1410":"1361–1410","1423":"1423","1400":"1400","1345":"1345","1410":"1410","31 July 1423":"31. juuli 1423","1454":"1454","1440":"1440","1361":"1361","1382":"1382","1380":"1380","Minto, Roxburghshire, Scotland":"Minto, Roxburghshire, Scotland","Lauder, Roxburghshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Roxburghshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Battle of Cravant, France":"Cravant, Loiret, Centre-Val de Loire, Prantsusmaa","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fi":{"1382–1440":"1382–1440","1380–Female":"1380–Kuollut","1400–Female":"1400–Kuollut","1410–1454":"1410–1454","1345–1423":"1345–1423","1361–1410":"1361–1410","1423":"1423","1400":"1400","1345":"1345","1410":"1410","31 July 1423":"31. heinäkuuta 1423","1454":"1454","1440":"1440","1361":"1361","1382":"1382","1380":"1380","Minto, Roxburghshire, Scotland":"Minto, Roxburghshire, Scotland","Lauder, Roxburghshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Roxburghshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Battle of Cravant, France":"Cravant, Loiret, Centre-Val de Loire, Ranska","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fr":{"1382–1440":"1382–1440","1380–Female":"1380–Décédée","1400–Female":"1400–Décédée","1410–1454":"1410–1454","1345–1423":"1345–1423","1361–1410":"1361–1410","1423":"1423","1400":"1400","1345":"1345","1410":"1410","31 July 1423":"31 juillet 1423","1454":"1454","1440":"1440","1361":"1361","1382":"1382","1380":"1380","Minto, Roxburghshire, Scotland":"Minto, Roxburghshire, Écosse","Lauder, Roxburghshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Roxburghshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","Battle of Cravant, France":"Cravant, Loiret, Centre-Val de Loire, France","Scotland"